Former Generations actor and Jozi FM DJ Mandla Hlatshwayo has been laid to rest at the Avalon Cemetery in Soweto. JOHANNESBURG - Former Generations actor and Jozi FM DJ Mandla Hlatshwayo has been laid to rest at the Avalon Cemetery in Soweto.The slain DJ was gunned down along with his friend Oupa Duma outside a pub in Soweto last Sunday, 7 May, while trying to help two women who'd been robbed.#MandlaHlatshwayo Memories are shared. TH pic.twitter.com/7NRz432HwFHlatshwayo s family has described him as a person always willing to help others.The family says it s hard to accept his death because it reminds them of hlatshwayo s late father, who was shot dead decades ago.Four men have been arrested in connection with the murder of Hlatshwayo and Duma.Jozi FM CEO Mpho Mhlongo says he ll never forget the day the famous DJ died. When I saw his body there on Sunday night I didn t want to believe it, I thought and hoped that they were pulling a prank. They took his shoes how dare they take his life and shoes? His cap was lying next to him. To think a few hours earlier we were having good time. WATCH: Mandla Hlatshwayo gunned down at Pimville pub(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)